text: Mo i Rana is a city in Nordland county, Norway. It is the administrative centre of the municipality of Rana. The city is in the Helgeland region. It is a few kilometers south of the Arctic Circle. In 2023, 25,980 people lived there, which makes it the largest city in Helgeland by population and the second largest city (after Bod√∏) in Nordland county by population.
